title: Grateful Dead Live at Nassau Coliseum on 1993-04-02
lineage: Schoeps MK41's > CMC5 > DAT > CDR > EAC (secure) > CD Wave > mkwACT > SHN (seekable)
description: Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower-> The Same Thing, Jack A Roe, Queen Jane Approximately, Brown Eyed Women, Picasso Moon Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Women Are Smarter, Terrapin Station-> Corinna-> Drums-> Jam-> The Last Time-> Black Peter-> Around & Around, E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text:
This Show Rules!! Why aren't there any other reviews here?  Am I the last one to discover this show?  The crowd singing along on the whole thing is kind of cool, but I'm a little worried that it'll make the show unlistenable after the 10th or 100th time. :-)

Help->slipknot->Franklin's...check it.

GREAT!!! What a great show for the time that it is in. the sound is pretty good for an audience recording. the second set is on fire! scarlet, fire, women smarter, and terrapin!  A definite DL for your 93 shows.
No. not a keeper in terms of AUD quality. sort the AUDs by rating and you'll find a bunch of better shows that cover most of what's covered here.

Good Memories I got into this show for FREE with a few of my friends - one of them knew a security guard. He brought us inside the building to the mezzanine, down to the floor, then placed us in the center aisle and said "don't move, or I'll have to throw you out." He placed me 9th row center in front of Bobby - why would I move?

It was by far the best setlist I had the pleasure of hearing live. Good times, good memories :)

love it!! my 150th show.  i love every second of this night.  btw, the quality is excellent!!! anyone who has been fortunate enough to see this band, would agree that this recording captures the essence.  great job whoever you are!!

Solid show. Walked into this show with high hopes. This was my first Dead show. IMO, a solid set.  I was 15 and took the train down from CT solo to meet some girls who had hooked me with a ticket. 
 I really felt lucky to witness such a killer performance.

2nd row floor!! Got super lucky on my mail order tickets ..2nd row floor - right in front of Jerry   ..I was 17 and even still remember falling in love with Black Peter .... I never really got it until I was 5 feet from Jerry. Still have the ticket stub ❤️
